<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910531-0029</DOCNO><DOCID>910531-0029.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Ziff-Davis Publishing Co.:   Three Magazines Planned   In Expansion Into Europe</HL><DATE>05/31/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4A</SO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)</IN><RE>EUROPE (EU)FRANCE (FR)GERMANY (GE)NEW YORK (NY)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)</RE><LP>   Ziff-Davis Publishing Co., the largest U.S. publisher ofcomputer industry publications, said it plans to expand intoEurope by launching three magazines.   The new publications, which will be launched in Germany,France and the United Kingdom this winter, are aimed atdirect buyers of personal computer products. In recent years,direct marketing of computer products has soared in the U.S.and New York-based Ziff-Davis says it expects thedirect-marketing approach will take off soon in WesternEurope. Ziff-Davis's future plans also include Asia and worldeditions.</LP><TEXT>   Ziff-Davis's current publications include ComputerShopper, PC Sources, PC Magazine, MacWeek and MacUser.</TEXT></DOC>